This 200-page report delves into the evolution of renewable energy, covering its historical context, technological advancements, and future prospects. It begins with a global overview of energy consumption trends and the rising need for sustainable sources due to climate change. Detailed chapters discuss various renewable sources like solar, wind, hydropower, and geothermal energy, examining their technological developments, efficiency metrics, and environmental impacts. The report also explores the economic aspects, including investment trends, market growth, and policy frameworks in different countries. It concludes with an analysis of challenges in integrating renewable energy into existing grids, the role of innovation in overcoming these challenges, and the potential impact on global economic structures.
